description: Try a fresh take on pizza for a quick and easy dinner. Naan bread is topped with satay sauce, tofu, kale and cheese for a fabulous twist on a takeaway favourite.
keywords: Mains,Seafood free,Egg free,Winter,Weeknight dinner,Aug 2021,Budget,Zucchini,High protein,High fibre,Kale,Tofu,Spinach
name: Satay Tofu Naan Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 2 cup Woolworths kale & spinach salad mix
200g Macro satay tofu, cut into wedges
1 small zucchini, halved lengthways, thinly sliced

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fanforced. Line a large baking tray with baking paper, then place in oven.

Spread naan breads with satay sauce. Place salad mix, tofu, onion, zucchini and cheese in a large bowl, then toss to combine. Top naan breads with tofu mixture. Transferto tray. Bake for 10 minutes or until golden and warmed through. Season with pepper and serve drizzled with sweet chilli sauce.
